trans-unit.source: By default, any class that inherits from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> uses UIElement3DAutomationPeer to communicate with [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)].

trans-unit.source: If you create a class that inherits from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>, you may want to provide an automation peer to support the functionality of your class.
trans-unit.target: Se criar uma classe que herda <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>, poderá pretender fornecer um ponto de automatização para suportar a funcionalidade da sua classe.</xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>

trans-unit.source: Override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A> method to return a string that represents the type of the element associated with the UIElement3DAutomationPeer.
trans-unit.target: Substituir o <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A>método para devolver uma cadeia que representa o tipo de elemento associado a UIElement3DAutomationPeer.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A>

trans-unit.source: For example, if you create a class called `My3DElement` and an automation peer called `My3DElementAutomationPeer`, override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A> method to return the string "My3DElement".
trans-unit.target: Por exemplo, se criar uma classe denominada `My3DElement` e um elemento de rede de automatização chamada `My3DElementAutomationPeer`, substituir o <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A>método para devolver a cadeia "My3DElement".</xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A>

trans-unit.source: If your class matches one of the known control types, override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetAutomationControlTypeCore%2A> method to return that <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType>.
trans-unit.target: Se a classe de corresponder a um dos tipos conhecidos de controlo, substitua o <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetAutomationControlTypeCore%2A>método para devolver essa <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType>.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetAutomationControlTypeCore%2A>

trans-unit.source: Note that although the existing <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> values are generally associated with 2D controls, the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> indicates a control's functionality, not its appearance.
trans-unit.target: Tenha em atenção que embora existente <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType>valores associados geralmente 2D controlos, o <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType>indica a funcionalidade de um controlo, não o aspecto.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType>

trans-unit.source: So if your <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> invokes an action when the user clicks it, you probably want <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetHelpTextCore%2A> to return <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType.Button?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Por isso, se sua <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>invoca uma ação quando o utilizador clica nele, provavelmente pretende <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetHelpTextCore%2A>devolver <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType.Button?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType.Button?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetHelpTextCore%2A> </xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>

trans-unit.target: O comportamento da sua personalizada <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>determina que outros métodos de devem substituir.</xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>
